> assistant
Yes — but before I suggest the exact change:

1. Are you okay with changing the diff flow to use a real temporary file for the preview side instead of a custom `convo-output:` virtual document?
2. Or do you specifically want to keep the `convo-output:` scheme and make that work correctly with a `TextDocumentContentProvider`?

Right now the blocker is that `workspace.fs.writeFile(previewUri,...)` will never route through a `TextDocumentContentProvider`. That provider only serves content when VS Code opens a document for that URI scheme; it does not make `workspace.fs` writable for custom schemes.


